animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to adoptioncenter@homewardtrails.org

Due to COVID-19 precautions, all animals for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. You can make an appointment to meet available dogs at our ADOPTION CENTER by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet and available cats at MEOW PALACE by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1. 
For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE: http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Tita just arrive from Puerto Rico! She is good with people and other dogs. Can you give her a forever home?

Adoption Coordinator: Homeward Trails Adoption Center
Location: Adoption Center
The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee DOES INCLUDE spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program

animal.description:
1. Adoption Fee $225 2. Application is found at www.fetchingfureverhomes.org 3. We do not "ship" our dogs. 4. Application process includes the app, meet and greet, home visit, minimum 24-hour overnight stay, adoption agreement.

Murphy is a sweet, sensitive 1 year old Pointer mix. He would love a fenced in back yard to follow his nose around. He loves to snuggle and goof around. Murphy rides nicely in the car. Murphy knows sit, stay, up, come and we are working on shake and lay down. He walks nicely on a leash using a Gentle Leader Head Halter. Murphy has completed 7 days of basic training with United Paws Dog Training. Murphy will require a home with experienced dog owners that can keep him active and out of trouble. He is a very high energy dog and needs to keep his mind busy and focused. He is dog friendly but unknown to cats. Since his energy level is so high, we would recommend a home with children 10 and older. *He also would love a back yard with a 6 foot fence.

animal.description: This is a very sweet girl that was rescued from the Waynesville animal shelter. She is crate trained and very well behaved. Bobbi Jo is up to date on all her shots, spayed, and microchipped. She is also almost housetrained, it shouldn't take long. After a few days of the new owner having this girl in her home she started going after her cat. She is heartbroken to have to give her up but doesn't feel that going back to the shelter environment is the best thing for her. If you would like more information or are interested in bringing this girl into your home please contact the current owner, Michelle, via email at michelle.pichardo89@gmail.com. Bobbi Jo is located in Shelby NC.

animal.description:
Hello sunshine! My name is Pheebs. I am a sweet, little Great Dane, who is looking to be the lady of the castle. I live for affection, and look forward to any tummy scratches I can get! I have a fairly moderate energy level for a dog my size. I am very well mannered, but a strong walker on a leash. I will definitely need a little bit of leash training with my new family. 

I absolutely adore people, and can be iffy with some dogs. I have a tendency to resource guard with other dogs, so I will absolutely need to be the only dog in the household.

 Because of my size and strength, I will not be able to go home with a family who has children under the age of 10. I know my basic commands, and again, will probably benefit from some training. I am housebroken, and looking for a place to call home. If you think you could be my person, please give the nice folks at MaxFund a call at 303-595-4917 so I can meet you!

**Because I am a pure bred Great Dane, my adoption fee will be $250**


MaxFund is a physical shelter located at 1005 Galapago St in Denver, Colorado.
If you are interested in learning more about a dog, please call 303-595-4917 to make an appointment

This PetFinder account is managed by volunteers, and the most up-to-date information is at the shelter.
How our adoption process works:
1. You MUST come into the shelter to meet a dog you are interested in (and meet a few others, while you’re at it!)
                              Our hours are 10-5 Mon, Wed, Thu Fri / 11-5 Saturday / 12-5 Sunday
                We suggest you call ahead to be sure the dog(s) do not have pending applications
2. You will fill out your adoption application, including references, after finding a dog you’d like to adopt
3. The application review and reference checks will take up to 3-5 business days; you will not be able to bring a dog home same-day
                We only take 2 applications per dog, before they are unavailable. This is why we suggest you call ahead to check the status of the pup!
 
We do not adopt out-of-state.
Thank you for choosing to rescue!

animal.description:
Meet Apollo! He is a 25 lbs, 1 year old dog who is maybe the cutest dog you've ever seen and maybe a Corgi. Admittedly, we have no idea if he's actually a Corgi mix but he's got the short stubby legs of a Corgi, he excels at "splooting" said stubby legs, he has the energy of a herding dog. Here are the top facts you need to know about Apollo straight from his foster mom:

-Apollo LOVES to play with other dogs. He plays hard and could spend all day wrestling, playing tug and running zoomies with another playful dog.
-Apollo is very cat friendly! He lives with a cat currently and is excellent with her.
-Apollo is very outgoing and social with people. He hasn't been around kids yet. We think he'd be fine with kids but he doesn't have many manners yet (puppy life) so he'll need some training.
-Apollo is mostly housebroken but he needs go to outside to potty about once per hour if he is outside of his kennel. If he doesn't get out to potty on the hour, he will still have some pee accidents inside. This is pretty easy to manage in a home with a fenced in yard but not so easy to manage in an apartment.
-Apollo is excellent in a crate! He stays in his crate while his foster family is at work and at bedtime and he is perfectly well behaved while kenneled.
-Apollo is the most fun dog ever and has the funniest personality!


If you're interested in meeting Apollo, please visit our website to learn about our adoption process and to fill out an application, www.gatewaypets.org/adopt

All of our dogs and cats will be micro-chipped, spayed or neutered, and up-to-date on vaccinations at the time of adoption. For more photos of Apollo, follow us on Facebook Gateway Pet Guardians and Instagram @gatewaypets ... #gpgApollo

To view other adoptable pets from our shelter, please visit, www.gatewaypets.org/adopt

Gateway Pet Guardians is proud to offer a variety of mixed breed dogs available for adoption. However, please keep in mind that we rarely know the genetic background of the animals we rescue and, as such, we cannot guarantee the exact breed combinations found within this dog. However, we do not know his/her actual genetic makeup. Just know that this dog is probably a variety of several different breeds that have combined to create one very amazing and unique animal.

He loves other dogs, plays fetch and will entertain everyone with his funny antics.  Ace would love a home with an active family and possibly a female dog who likes to romp around as much as he does.  He will need a lot of exercise and stimulation.  Ace is working on manner training with our volunteers and is eager to please.  He is great on walks and loves his treats.  Ace is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped.  Who wouldn’t want this smiley boy as a part of his family!?!?!

If you are interested in Ace, please go to bfdaaa.com to complete an application.

However, due to Bella not currently being spayed out of state applicants will not be considered. 

Bella's needs: Fenced yard. Doggy dog access a plus. A verifiable  excellent vet reference. Another playful dog in the home a plus.

Bella is an 8 to 9 month old female "Shepherd Mix" per her vet records. However she is only 16 pounds and suspect she is either Sheltie or a Border Collie type mix.

She per her foster family is friendly, playful and social. She knows sit and down.

Housebroken with a schedule.

Please do not email questions. All viable applications will be forwarded to Bella's foster Mom.

animal.description:
NOTE: This is a courtesy posting for another rescuer. Please do not contact ARRF, as we do not know this pet personally. To meet BRUTUS, see the contact information below.

Brutus is a beautiful, sweet 1-year-old Shepherd/Akita mix who was rescued off the streets of Tijuana.  He is a lot of dog, but in a good way. Brutus is a neutered male and weighs about 75 lbs. 

He is very inquisitive, eager to learn, and ready for fun. He is calm, playful, and loving, yet protective.  He gets along well with other dogs and people. Brutus is housetrained and knows how to use a doggie door. He would be great with an individual or family who is active. He is ready to learn new things and he loves to ride in the car.  

In addition to being neutered, Brutus has been wormed, microchipped, and is up-to-date with his Distemper/Parvo, Bordetella, and Rabies shots. He has been given Nexgard flea treatment.  

An application for adoption will be requested, along with a video of your yard. There is a rehoming fee, and medical records will be provided. To meet Brutus, email, call, or text his foster mom: Pam.Lawless@gcccd.edu; 619.964.1181.

animal.description:
S.P.C.A. Albrecht Center For Animal Welfare
 Requirements for Adoption
1. Most of our dogs will require a fenced in yard to allow them to play safely outdoors.
2. If you have other pets in the home, you will need to provide proof of current rabies vaccines.
3. If you rent your home, we will need to verify that you have your landlord’s approval for the pet.
4. If you have other pets, we strongly encourage you to bring them to the shelter to meet the animal you wish to adopt first, to make sure everyone will get along.
The S.P.C.A. Albrecht Center for Animale Welfare adoption fees vary. Please call the shelter for each pet's adoption fee. 803-648-6863. Adoption fees include age-appropriate vaccinations, deworming, spay/neuter and microchip implantation and registration. Heartworm testing and treatment is also included for adult dogs. love

animal.description:
Spot is a big, jolly fellow that always seems to be smiling! Once you get to know him he loves pets and the occasional snuggles. He will flop over for belly rubs and won't want you to stop! When outside he is in adventure mode and wants nothing more than to keep exploring. He enjoys getting the zoomies and playing outside just as much as the next dog but when push comes to shove, he'd rather spend his time relaxing and thinking about his next big adventure while playing with a toy. 

Spot came to Lollypop Farm because his previous home wasn't a good fit. During his time with us, Spot has shown that it can take a little time for him to call you his pal, but once he does you will be his new best friend! Spot isn't the biggest fan of sharing his toys or high value items but has been learning how to exchange items for treats or other items and he'd love to show you! 

The recommendations for Spot's success is a home that has no children under the age of 14. He has a history living with another dog but we are unaware of how they interacted together. Since Spot takes a little more time to be comfortable with new people, it will require more than one visit before taking him home. 
 
If you'd like to meet Spot you can set up an appointment with Gillian via email at gfralick@lollypop.org!

Meet Bella!

Just LOOK at that BEAUTIFUL golden/red coat!  She knows some of her commands such as sit, down, and come.  And you will be happy to know that she is calm and gentle.

Bella is intelligent, active and affectionate. She loves to go for walks, and she's good on a leash. She LOVES all people and gets along well with other dogs.

Bella was rescued from a patio where she was left alone to fend for herself in the blaring heat of the Puerto Rico sun.

We heard about this bright, beautiful girl, and knew we had to help! She is now at our shelter in NH, looking for her forever family. She's confident, and absolutely wonderful with people.

Bella is about 1 year old, and she weighs 45 lbs. She is spayed, has all her required vaccines, and is microchipped.

If you'd like to open your heart and home to this BEAUTY-ful girl, please complete an adoption application at https://www.heartsandtails.org/adoption-application/

PLEASE NOTE that due to the overwhelming number of inquiries we receive daily, we can only respond to those who have completed an online application, and appear to be a good match. PLEASE check all of the fields in this profile to ensure your question hasn't already been answered as most of the information is in this profile.

animal.description:
Age: ~ 2 years (as of 01/20/21)
Weight: 91.6 lbs (as of 01/20/21)

This dog has been spayed/neutered, is up to date on shots, on heartworm preventative and is microchipped.

Chloe is a big sweet girl!

She is also playful and smart. We are thinking this gorgeous girl is a Lab and Great Dane mix about 2 years old with a beautiful shinny coat.

Chloe is friendly with all of us humans including kids, but she is a big playful girl that may be too much for young children. She is sociable with other dogs but tends to prefer male doggies over females. We don't know if this is with all female dogs or selectively. She seems ok with cats and will track in a playful way. Chloe is pretty quiet but may alert bark to get your attention.

She has mainly been an outdoor dog and is not house trained or crate trained but have a feeling she will be a quick study as she is such an intelligent girl! A fenced yard would be ideal so she could run and play safely, but she does sometimes dig if left alone. If a fenced yard is not available, she'll need lots of leash walks and opportunities for off-leash play in a fenced area.

A potential adopter should be prepared to give her regular exercise, a structured routine, work on socialization, and couple all of these things with lots of praise and treats! An obedience course is a must with Chloe; it will help teach her good manners and commands, further socialization with other dogs and people, and will help build that very important bond between a dog and her human.

Chloe a gentle happy girl who just wants a loving forever home. Can you make her dream come true? Fill out an application today and let her know that you'd love to have her join your family!

Medical Note:

This dog tested positive for exposure to ehrlichia while in SOS foster care. This does not mean that this dog had ehrlichia. This dog is/has been asymptomatic while in SOS care and was preventatively treated with a 28-day course of doxycycline. Please see here for more information on ehrlichia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ehrlichiosis_(canine). Please check with your vet if you should have any questions or concerns about this condition, and discuss any concerns you may have with your SOS Adoption Counselor.

Adoption Fee: $585

To apply for this dog, fill out an adoption application on our website: www.sosarl.org/aa/

**Additional info you should know - For most of our dogs, we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each of our dogs as an individual and do our best to describe and place them based on personality not breed label. Some dogs may not yet be in New England, nor ready for immediate adoption. There may be additional vetting, quarantine, waiting periods and/or fees depending upon your state of residence. If you have questions or concerns on any of this, you can discuss this with your Adoption Counselor.

Jessie/Paco is a fun loving, very energetic guy. Everything is a game to him until you tell him no . Even then he looks at you in a way that makes you doubt if you're right. He is fearful of most men so you will need to be patient with him. He is crate trained , will need a little work on signaling at the door for outside time. He loves cuddling when he finally slows down. Loves attention and playing with toys. He is very handsome but still needs training on manners. He walks good on a leash but is very powerful when walking . He wants to play with small dogs but at this time is too rough . He is all puppy all the time. Since he is an active pup, he needs a fenced in yard so he can run and play.
He is 45lb, up to date on vaccinations, heartworm negative, on prevention, neutered and microchipped. His adoption fee is $150

The fastest way to get the ball rolling is to complete an adoption application for the dog that caught your eye. Thank you for considering the adoption of a shelter dog!

animal.description:
Midnight is a 12 year old spaniel mix. He's about 33 pounds, and he's looking for a very special home to love him for all of his days! Midnight is at the point in his life where he is well past the excitement that life with multiple animals and small children has to offer. An ideal home for him would be one without any hustle or bustle. He would love a home of his own where all of the attention is on him.

This handsome boy isn't just a couch potato, though! Sure, he enjoys the occasional Netflix binge and lazy Sunday morning like the rest of us, but at 12 years old he still has a spring in his step and a taste for adventure! He's lively and zippy and has such a funny personality that keeps us all entertained and laughing.

Midnight's adoption fee is $195, and he is neutered, microchipped and current on all vaccines.

What do you say? Are you in need of the love only Midnight can offer? We think so, too. Apply online today to adopt Midnight! Applications are available at www.partnersforpetsil.org/applications

animal.description:
Finn is a beautiful 2 to 3 year old, & 45lb Beagle/Yellow Lab mix, according to the Texas vets. (This is just an educated guess, he probably has multiple breeds in him!) with all the traits that make these super- smart and personality-plus dogs very popular breed mixes for families and individuals searching for loving and loyal best friends. Finn was found as a stray in Texas and has been staying with a foster until he comes to Colorado to find his forever home. 

The following is from his foster: 
“Oh, my sweetest foster I’ve had! He is a beautiful lab/Beagle mix. He looks like butter and this boy will melt your heart!  He loves all people, all dogs, all children! He is not a cuddler but loves attention and getting pets. He is crate trained, house trained, and sleeps through night without any problem. He goes right out to pee and does his business in the privacy of the bushes. A true gentleman. He is not aggressive at all with food and really never acts too hungry. He loves to play in the hose and is not afraid of  water. That’s the lab in him. Now for the other breeds in him - besides his mottled tongue and curled up tail. He is always looking for cats, birds, and squirrels in trees when outside. He marks his territory often (outside only, luckily) but has not peed on a thing inside my house! He does nicely on the leash and does NOT pull my arm out of it's socket! He smiles to greet me after I have left him in his crate and genuinely likes everything! Not needy! I have not tried leaving him in my house without a crate.  He loves a car ride and jumps right in and stays in the back of the car without any problem. I’ve seen no chewing. He adores chasing tennis balls. He has lots of strong energy but uses it well. It’s EASY to love this buttery boy!”

While Finn will be initially shy when he arrives on transport in Colorado, a bit of time, kindness and yummy treats will quickly bring this guy out of his shell. We know that this sweet dog enjoys his time with his Texas foster dad and mom tremendously.. his favorite times of the day are the times spent together. When he arrived at their home, however, he was frightened and just a bit watchful. With some time to sort things out, Finn was quickly a lover.. and ultimately a best friend. His foster is very clear that this gorgeous guy is over the top sweet, a bit shy at first.. but once comfortable,..the most loving guy ever!

Farfel's Rescue would like to see Finn in a home where he'll get consistent mental stimulation, exercise and tons of loving hugs. A positive reinforcement/force free group training class promotes great behavior, bonding and confidence for a young guy whose self-esteem will fly high while he masters his skills. Farfel's feels so strongly about a training opportunity for all dogs that we're unwilling to adopt to a family that doesn't choose to give Finn this opportunity. Farfel's is happy to provide a list of approved positive reinforcement/force free trainers in your area.

Finn will be arriving on transport in Denver on Wednesday 2/3/2021. We're currently searching for a very loving, nurturing and committed family for our wonderful Finn. Applications are being accepted for this loyal and devoted best friend and can be found at http://farfels.com/farfels-rescue/adoption-form/. If interested, please fill out completely and submit.

**PLEASE NOTE** Farfel's Rescue makes serious efforts to place our dogs with families that are excellent matches. We do this through our Farfel's Rescue application found at the link above or at farfels.com (never through rescue site apps such as Adoptapet or Petfinder as they don't provide enough information). If you're truly interested in adopting Finn please be sure to fill out the Farfel's Rescue adoption application. It's the only initial tool that we have to determine a great match for this very deserving guy. We're sorry, but in most cases, we're unable to get back to those that don't submit a Farfel's Rescue application. Thanks very much for choosing rescue.
animal.name: Finn

animal.description:
Merlin is a young, neutered, charming and handsome Boxer Boy!  Merlin has suffered some mistreatment in his life and did find himself in a male dog aggressive environment.  He has carried that programming with him, though he was just neutered on January 20, 2021.  

Shots, worming and vet care provided by Ozark Haven Rescue thus his adoption donation will be provided directly to them as well.

Merlin does well with smaller dogs, female dogs, neutered dogs, most cats and livestock..  He is totally housebroken, leash trained, crate trained and tends towards territorialism.  

Merlin is pretty crafty with finding weaknesses in common fenced yards.  A safety plan for him and the neighborhood is required.  

An ideal home for Merlin would be Boxer experienced empty nesters with a strong vet and training history with the breed or other powerful breeds.  A healthy respect is mandatory for this magnificent beast!   Apartment dwellers welcome and a work from home jogger would be awesome!!!

In the right home Merlin will flourish and share years and years of love and companionship!

animal.description:
Rocco is a typical Chihuahua. He is very fearful at first. All he needs is some time to get to know you. He would do better in an adult home without any small children. Rocco is not friendly when he meets new people but with calm and baby talk, you can win him over in a few minutes, Rocco is a cuddler who enjoys sitting on the sofa with you or just cuddles next to you in bed. 

He would make the perfect quarantine partner for someone who is looking for a loving Chihuahua. He walks well on the leash. He does well with other big or little calm dogs. He can be a bit possessive of his human but that is typical behavior of a Chihuahua who loves his owners. Rocco really enjoy going out in the yard and taking in that sun. Rocco doesn't like loud noise or loud people so keep in mind, he needs a soft spoken family who is willing to share their loving home with this perfect little Chihuahua. 

Rocco is neutered, microchipped, frontline, heartworm negative, fully vetted and just got a dental. His adoption fee is $500. 
Broward County and West Palm Beach Adoption ONLY! No out of state adoptions. If you are interested for a meet and greet, you must fill out an adoption application FIRST. (Absolutely no exceptions) Apply here: https://naiasrescue.org/ or contact (786) 263-8323 or email naiaspetrescue@gmail.com

She is about 7-8 yrs old, about 40-45 lbs, completely house broken, is crate trained but can be left out alone in the home because she is very well behaved. We can’t understand how someone could walk away from such a sweet and loving girl…but we aren’t going to focus on that anymore. We happily took her in to rescue to find her real forever home. animal.description:
Meet Rip! This lump of love is being fostered with a family (and other pups!) south of Boston. Says his foster mom"Rip is a dream! He is a playful pup, loves my dogs and my kids, and is a master snuggler. He is working on potty training and does go every time he is brought outside. Overall, he is a well rounded pup and his hazel eyes and chocolate coat will win your heart!"

Read through our adoption process and other adoption FAQs here www.rescueinc.dog/FAQs

All of our pups come with the following: 


	Spayed or Neutered
	Age appropriate vaccinations + dewormed + 4DX test (if older than 6 months)
	New martingale collar with 6' lead + temp ID tag
	30 days free insurance to be activated within 24 hours of your wellness visit with your veterinarian
	Microchip with free registration for your new pup, but also for any other pets in your household too!
	Southern pups, younger than 6 months, come with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm prevention to prevent any lapse of protection 
	Our southern dogs, 6 months and older, come with a **Proheart 6 injection which provides 6 months of Heartworm protection (approx value of $100) + dose of flea / tick preventative


**dogs surrendered to us in MA do not recieve the Proheart 6 injection but do go home with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm preventative so there is no lapse in protection

Ages listed can be approximate and breed mixes are a best guess based on physical characteristics. 

If you are seeing this listing on Petfinder, please apply through the link on our website at www.rescueinc.dog/adopt 

Please do not email with questions or message through Petfinder. Communication with the rescue always starts with submitting an application. 

If you see this listing, the pup is still available. We pull listings after 2 to 3 viable applications are submitted.

animal.description:
Male, ~1 year old, ~16 lbs.

Please note that our rescue serves only Washington DC, Maryland, and northern Virginia as we require home visits of all applicants. If you are outside this area, we will not process your application.

Approximate Age:

~1 year old

Approximate Weight/Size:

Small

Good with:

Dogs

Not tested with:

Kids, Cats

Hi, I'm Simon! I'm an easygoing pup who loves being inside with the humans I love. I don't really like going on walks -- I prefer to go in and out and then come back inside to get nice and warm on the sofa. I would love a quiet home where I can be with my family often. Maybe a nice home with a retiree where I'm not left alone often. I just want to snuggle and get pets and I can't wait to find a forever home where I can share all the love I've got to give!

Adoption Application:

http://bit.ly/adoptrdr

Adoption Application:
http://bit.ly/adoptrdr

Foster Application: http://bit.ly/fosterapprdr

Adoption Process: In order to adopt, we require an adoption application. After you submit an application, if you pass the screening, we will contact you to schedule a phone interview. We will call your references, including your veterinarian and landlord (when appropriate). We will also conduct a home visit. After these steps are complete, you will be approved to adopt a dog. Please note this process takes 1-2 weeks so applications submitted when you are ready to bring a dog home within that time frame. You can meet our adoptable dogs at events, however, we cannot guarantee that dogs at events do not have pre-approved applicants meeting them there as well, so the application is the best way to start the process.

Mission Statement: Forever true to "The Underdog", Rural Dog Rescue is dedicated to saving the lives of dogs in shelters who are often overlooked for adoption or rescue. We save the dogs who are at most risk of being euthanized: the hounds, the black dogs, the seniors, the sick and the broken. We make a commitment to reserve a minimum of 50% of the dogs we save to The Underdog. Root For The Underdog!

Rural Dog Rescue's home base is in Washington, DC. We adopt to the Washington, DC metropolitan area to include Maryland and Northern Virginia.

We support several high kill shelters that euthanize in 72 hours and whose kill rate is 70% or higher in rural areas of Virginia, West Virginia, North and South Carolina. Rural Dog Rescue also helps dogs in need in Washington, DC and Maryland.

We are 100% volunteer and foster based and no salaries are paid. 100% of your donation and adoption fee goes to helping the dogs and cats of Rural Dog Rescue.

Although we try to be as accurate as possible, Rural Dog Rescue cannot guarantee the breed or full-grown adult size of any of the dogs or puppies in its care. Because many of these dogs were found as strays or are the result of irresponsible, unplanned breeding, we do not know the dog's exact background and can only list breed and size by our best educated guess. If exact breed and size are important to you, please consider adopting a dog from a specific breed rescue. Our goal is for our dogs to be adopted by people who will love and care for them forever for who they are - no matter what breed and size they turn out to be!

All dogs go to their new homes spayed or neutered, up to date on all shots, dewormed (although a second deworming may be required), started on heartworm and flea and tick preventative and sometimes microchipped.

Our rescue group took her and her 4 adorable siblings into our group after they had been abandoned behind a building

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Did I catch your eye? Learn more about me by reading my profile below; I just might be your new best friend! Apply on our website
(

https://www.healingheartsrescue.org/adopt

)

to

set up a private meeting or check below for my adoption event schedule.

Age: Estimated DOB 11/28/2020

Dog friendly: Yes

Cat friendly: Yes

Kid friendly: Yes

Potty trained: No, I'm just a puppy

Crate trained: No, I'm just a puppy

Meet Renly.

He's a whole lot of personality in a small package!

Renly loves to play, romp around and be an all out sassy puppy. He loves playing with his toys and the big dogs, even though he is still a little afraid of how big they are. Renly is an adventurous boy with a lot of puppy energy.

Renly is crate trained for overnight and potty pad trained but he is also working on traditional potty training now that he's old enough.

Renly had an umbilical hernia when he was born that was corrected in rescue. He is the last puppy in his litter to be adoptable, which gave us more time to work on individual training with him.

He has black colored fur with a tiny white chest marking and super sweet puppy eyes. He was born in Missouri, to a black lab mom, his dad is most likely a husky that lived near by. The litter of pups were surrendered to rescue.

Renly is 9 weeks old as of 1/31/21.

He is one of 8 puppies in his litter.

He hopes his next adventure is to find a forever family of his own!

Adoption Fee: $495

INTERESTED IN MEETING ME?

If you'd like to arrange a private meeting or begin the adoption process, please fill out an adoption application by visiting

https://www.healingheartsrescue.org/adopt

**Note on breed and age determination:

Breed and age are often determined on appearance, our own knowledge, veterinarian advice, and/or information from the sending shelters or previous owners. Most of our adoptable dogs were previously stray dogs with little history, we can't be 100% sure of a dog's breed mix, and unless there is a specific date of birth listed, we can't be 100% sure of a dog's age. Additionally, our assessments of a dog's interactions with other dogs, cats, or children are based on OUR experiences. Your experience may differ.

ADOPTION FEE INCLUDES:

Wellness check

Spay/neuter (puppies adopted with required spay/neuter certificate)

Age appropriate vaccines - rabies as required by law and distemper combo or proof of positive titer test

Heartworm test if over 7 months of age

Fecal test and/or deworming for parasites

Microchip



~ Healing Hearts rescue will also provide dental procedures, bloodwork, surgeries, and/or any other additional vet work as needed while dogs are in our care.

~ Adoption fees are non-negotiable and fees are listed on the dog's profile

~ Adoption fees can be paid the following ways with the required sales tax (7.525%) added:

PayPal

Credit Card

Cash

WANT TO HELP SAVE MORE DOGS?

Healing Hearts Rescue is a nonprofit, foster-based rescue

located in the Twin Cities area of Minnesota

that is 100% funded through adoption fees and donations

. We are excited for you to join us on this mission to save the lives of dogs in need.

We believe every dog deserves to be loved as true members of a family and are committed to fulfilling that dream one dog at a time! Sign up to foster, volunteer or donate on our
website

Healing Hearts rescue will also provide dental procedures, bloodwork, surgeries, and/or any other additional vet work as needed while dogs are in our care.

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for puppies covers initial deworming,  puppy vaccinations, microchip, and spay/neuter at the rescue's approved vet at 6 months of age. Please see our website for more information.

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
My name is Polar Bear. I am a one year old husky /mastiff mix (I'm told) and unfortunately looking for a new home.
I had a great home, got a human sister, and things got ugly between my people. As loved as I am by my mom, she was forced to give me up for very personal reasons. I am hoping my new family will give her updates. I heard this will be allowed and welcomed.

I am a big boy, and a very good boy. I'm very submissive, great with kids and other dogs. Due to Covid-19, sterilization will be done later, but for a non neutered male, I am great. I do however have one main issue : food allergies. If I get into anything not "approved " I will blotch out and get very itchy. 
I will have to live in a home that will be very strict with my diet. Right now, I am in rough shape as I got my mouth on some great stuff, but not for me. Duck is my food, and everything else is no good!

I am gentle, but young, so energetic. I need some training on walks, greeting people and responding to commands. I'm just a big goof at heart.

If you think you're the ideal human (s) for me and understand what a huge commitment adopting a dog is, then please hurry on over to www.sophiesdogadoption.com and download the adoption form. DO NOT just write in asking if I'm still available. You'll lose precious time. If you can see this bio, it means I'm still available.

animal.description:
Oliver is a little senior boy who was surrendered to a shelter after their German Shepherd attacked and injured him. Though he seems fearful of people at first, he will warm up with patience and will then seek out affection. So an adoption meet and greet may not result in Oliver in your lap giving you kisses but it will happen in time.

Once he trusts you he will be on your lap giving kisses and will follow you around everywhere! His foster mom reports that he even allowed her to trim his nails for him. He's watchful of new people but is a sweetheart once he knows he is safe. He seems to enjoy having a dog friend to explore and relax with, but not a big player yet. This little guy enjoys the companionship of felines as well. Oliver would love to have a "stay at home" person. He walks great on a leash and loves to explore. Oliver crates well and is house trained. If you can offer Oliver a quiet, patient and loving home please apply to adopt!

If you are interested in adopting Oliver, please complete an application at https://www.circle2rescue.com/dog-adoption-application/ The adoption fee of $259 includes the spay/neuter, vaccinations, deworming and microchip. 

Please note, Circle 2 Rescue cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have no history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

Nugget is a fun and playful pup with a zest for life. He's had some hard times, but doesn't let that get him down. He is high energy and always up for a game of tug or a run around the yard but will also burrow under the blankets and take a snooze on the couch. With other dogs, he can be a bit too excited and forceful which has led to some scuffles but he is not aggressive towards them. He knows his manners but sometimes gets too excited and forgets them. He's fully house trained and crate trained and will let you know when he needs to go out. He loves to play with balls, especially squeaky ones, and will have a hard time deciding which ones he wants to play with.

Please Note: All dogs are posted until they are officially adopted. This dog may have other interested adopters in line. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website at www.lasthopek9.org.

Questions? Please email adoptions@lasthopek9.org. For more photos, or information on upcoming adoption events where you can meet her, please go to www.lasthopek9.org or go to our Facebook page. Thank you for your interest in saving a life!

animal.description:
YOU MUST HAVE AN APPROVED APPLICATION IN ORDER TO MEET OUR PETS.

Angel is a sweet approximately 13 year old senior looking for a retirement home.  She was pulled from a local shelter after being found as a stray.  She was an overweight 62 pounds and could barely walk.  Since being in her foster home, she has lost some weight and is moving around much better though she needs to lose more.  Her ideal weight is probably around 52 pounds.

We do not know her breed mix, maybe Lab/Cattle Dog/Corgi in the blend??

Angel gets along with other dogs but can get a little over excited so another calm dog should be fine in her new home.  She does not move fast so any dog can easily get away from her if needed.

She seems to be house trained and will bark (howl) when she needs to go out.  

She sleeps a lot but does still enjoy playing with toys.

She loves to lie in the sun and wander around a fenced yard. She does like to take short walks but has a very slow, toddling walk.

Naturally, since she is a senior, Angel has some manageable medical issues. She may have old cruciate tears in both knees and arthritis. She is on Gabapentin, Ostifen and ArthriEase Gold tablets.  She has a small eyelid mass and takes medications for conjunctivitis.  Her eye lenses are cloudy, but she seems to be able to see everything she needs to see just fine. She came to us with flea allergy dermatitis but her hair is growing back now that she is flea free.  Her foster family is giving her omega oils and high quality food. She has a few typical old dog fatty tumors, not a problem. She has some rectal cysts but surgery to biopsy and remove those would be a very hard and painful recovery with a high risk of infection and painful bowel movements so we decided to just leave those alone.  Foster mom puts a little pumpkin in her morning meal to soften her stools.

Angel needs a one story house and cannot walk up more than one stair. Her foster family built her a little ramp to get into the house.

Adoption donation $125.


Please note that we do not ship animals. We also require a home visit before finalizing any adoptions so preference is given to applicants within a 90 mile range. You will be required to come to High Point, NC to meet/pick up your new pet.

HOW TO APPLY:
1. Go to www.lovingpetinnadoptions.org
2. Click on the "Adoption Application" link on the left side of the page.
3. The application will open as a PDF and you should have the ability to fill it in from that page. Be sure to complete all fields.
4. Save the application to your computer, then attach in an email and send to petprojectnc@gmail.com
5. Someone will review your application as soon as possible, usually within 24 hours, and will be in touch with next steps.

Hounds in Pounds strongly prefers yards that are fully fenced in by chain link, wrought iron or privacy fencing. Rock walls or tree lines are not acceptable forms of fencing. Homes with no fences will be evaluated on a case-by-case basis. Invisible fencing is not acceptable. We do not adopt out to homes with electric fences. Applications received that do not meet our fencing guidelines will not be considered.

animal.description:
LOOKING FOR THE ADOPTION APPLICATION FORM? 
Please visit our website at: www.LHAR.dog 

If application is approved, pup will be held for you to meet/adopt within a few days of application approval! 


(Appointment will be scheduled after application is approved) 

Location: WagsMore Adopt & Shop
                  450 Prospect Blvd, Frederick MD 21701
 
Age of pup: approx 6 months old of February 2021
   
The adoption donation for these pups: is $375.00

This includes: Age appropriate vaccines and dewormings, rabies vaccine, HW prevention and neuter

Size:  large when full grown 
Breed: Retriever mix is best guess?

Petfinder's Dog Size Recommendations:

Small: 25 lbs and under (11 kg)
Medium: 26–60 lbs (12 – 27 kg)
Large: 61–100 lbs (28 – 45 kg)
Extra Large: 101 lbs or more (46 kg)

Please note our requirements to adopt a young puppy. 

1. Fill out our online application at: Www.LHAR.dog 

2. We require all current pets in the household to be up to date on shots and be spayed/neutered. Veterinary references will be contacted. 

3. We require that someone be in the home/work from home half of the work day throughout the work week. It is not healthy for a puppy to be crated and left alone for 5 or more hours a day. Lunch breaks are not considered home half the work day and asking a neighbor to stop in is not considered home half the day. 

Their Story: 

LHAR rescued this happy pup with the help of an organization in rural WV. He is a goofy boy with a lot of energy. Loves other dogs and kids. We have no confirmed history of Mom or Dad. We believe he is a lab mix. Will do best in a home with an active family, a fenced in yard, and older children, 
He is being fostered in a private home 

Weight: approx 55 lbs as of February 1st         
 
Photos were taken on January 31st    

Questions? Please email: lharinfo@gmail.com

Adoption donation fees: Please know that 100% of our fees go towards the rescue of puppies and dogs in need. Lonely Hearts Animal Rescue is a 501c3 non profit organization.

Thank you for considering a rescue pup!

animal.description:
*WE ONLY DO HOME VISITS FOR ADOPTIONS NEAR BROWARD & PALM BEACH COUNTIES*

Slowly give a gentle hug to shy Adira. Her name means Strong, and Noble. We gave her this name to help her self-confidence. She is a retired breeder mama. Adira is 2 year old/50lbs English BullGirl given up to a vets office who turned her over to our rescue. Her spirit has been hurt by her previous people, but her playful loving personality still pops out occasionally. She will play with her toys and then looks around to make sure she is allowed to have fun. She will run in the fenced yard galloping like a horse then suddenly stops to hide as if she thinks she shouldn’t act happy! More and more she is opening to human love and her personality is starting to shine. She is absolutely loving and becoming more confident. She is puppy playful and has some puppy behavior she is working on. Adira weighs almost 50 lbs. She is very shy and timid so an adult home would be better suited for her needs. She needs a home where they will show her it's ok to trust and be loved. Loud noises scare her so soft-spoken people would be best. Adira does seem to like women better than men, only cowering to men she does not react, just tries to make herself as small as possible, covering her eyes. She will need some guidance, love, and patience in order for her to come out of her shell.

She needs a home with people who have experience with English bulldogs, understand all their breed characteristics and health concerns. She is healthy now but may have allergies or breathing issues in the future. We just want people to be prepared long term. She is good with smaller dogs and some taller dogs but she really prefers to be the only dog to ensure her feelings of safety. She does guard her food from other dogs so feeding separately would be necessary if you have another dog.

This dog's adoption fee is $900 to go towards their vetting (vaccines, spay/neuter, heartworm/Ehrlichia/Lyme test, fecal test, pre-op blood work, dental cleaning, and microchip as well as grooming if needed). 

If you are interested please fill out the adoption application For additional information regarding our adoption process or for a meet and greet, you must fill out an adoption application FIRST. Apply here: https://www.getalifepetrescue.com/
or you can call 954-629-2445 or email info@getalifepetrescue.com

Meet Tilly-

Simply put, Tilly is just cute all around! From day one Tilly has been a delight. She is such a happy puppy- ready to adventure or just chill if that's what's going on at the moment. She likes to get her wiggles out by playing fetch in the backyard or running laps with her brother. Tilly will never say no to a friendly wrestling match too! She likes to chew on toys to pass the time away and is a professional napper.  Tilly is highly social and the life of the party. She's good with a butt and tail jiggle to greet you as you come home. She's curious in all the right ways and is a quick learner. Tilly loves to be where the action is and playing outside. When it's time to relax, she loves to cuddle up on the sofa and extra bonus if someones getting work done on the computer next to her! Tilly is a wonderful puppy ready to bring joy and love to your home!
If you would like to meet Tilly, please visit spotslaststop.org and fill out an application.

ESTIMATED DOB:  2012
WEIGHT: 25 lbs
KIDS: Yes, Older
DOGS: Maybe
CATS: No

HISTORY: 
Luci and Snickers came to us from one of our rescue partners in Louisiana.  They were deeply loved pets who needed to find a new home after both of their owners passed away.

ABOUT:
Snickers and Luci have spent their entire lives together, we will require that they be adopted together as a bonded pair. Snickers is very friendly with people and is sooo happy when her fosters return from their day away and even sings a little “happy song” to show her excitement.   She whines a little bit when they leave, but eventually settles in and (probably) naps the day away while she waits. Snickers and Luci enjoy the occasional play session together but are generally low energy dogs.  Snickers and Luci would probably love to snuggle up in their foster’s bed, but they are content to share a bed on the floor.  Snickers and Luci  are very friendly with people and are being fostered with a teenager.  Snickers has fur that will require regular grooming appointments to keep it trimmed and clean.

Snickers and Luci are two easy going, well behaved girls who will make great companions for their new family.  They will be good girls while you are gone, they will be happy to see you when you are home, and they’re content to entertain themselves (with naps) when you’re busy. 

Interested in adding one of our adoptables to your family?  More information and our adoption application can be found at www.luluslockerrescue.org.

animal.description:
Meet Ollie!

He’s a Great Pyrenees mix, and based on the size of his paws, he’s going to be medium to large when he grows up. He’s currently living with a foster family that runs a doggy daycare, so he’s well socialized. Ollie loves all the dogs and people he meets. He loves play time, but when he gets tired he finds his favorite spot on a large dog bed and takes a break from the action. He’s doing great with his potty training. Ollie sits by the sliding door, and even lets out a bark once in a while to let his fosters know he needs to go outside. At the end of the day he’s ready for bed, and he has no problem sleeping through the night. This little guy is going to be a joy for his forever family!

Meet Lucy! Lucy is a senior boxer mix who doesn’t let her age define her personality. Lucy came to animal control with a tumor that was open and very large. It was clear that for quality of life, it had to be removed. It weighed 2 lbs. She had a literal weight lifted off her and she started her new lease on life. Pathology reports came back and were our worst fears- mast cell cancer. Lucy is considered a hospice case due to her age and the nature of mast cell BUT with her spunky attitude and penchant for long conversations with her humans, we know she will thoroughly enjoy the time she has left. 

Lucy is looking for someone who won’t mind a free loader who likes to sleep in. Someone with good food and who will listen to her great  stories. She loves to have conversations! Someone who will help her make and complete her bucket list. Is it you?

For more info text Courtney at 847-274-4240 or email us at care@pawsandaffectrescue.org

animal.description:
FOSTERED IN: Hampshire, IL 60140
ESTIMATED DOB:  2012
WEIGHT: 18 lbs
KIDS: Yes, Older
DOGS: Maybe
CATS: No

HISTORY: 
Luci and Snickers came to us from one of our rescue partners in Louisiana.  They were deeply loved pets who needed to find a new home after both of their owners passed away.

ABOUT:
Luci and Snickers have spent their entire lives together, we will require that they be adopted together as a bonded pair.  Luci’s foster home says she loves to be pet and has the softest fur to make it even more enjoyable.  Luci will sit on your lap and eat up your attention as long as you let her.  She is overall a low energy dog and is content to spend the workday alone napping, but is very happy and excited when her fosters get home.  Luci and Snickers would probably love to snuggle up in their foster’s bed, but they are content to share a bed on the floor.  Luci and Snickers are very friendly with people and are being fostered with a teenager.  Luci likes to herd on occasion, so any dogs that she would live with would need to be very tolerant of this behavior, their ideal home would have no other dogs.  We also do not think she would be appropriate to live with children who are too young to understand this herding behavior.  Younger, supervised visitors would be appropriate.  We do not know how Luci and Snickers are with cats, but because Luci likes to herd we would not feel comfortable adopting them to homes with cats.  Luci and Snickers have a fenced yard and do really well with that option.  Her foster home in Louisiana said Luci is a “runner” if she gets out without a leash so she should always be on a leash when not in a secure fenced area.  (This is required for all of our adopted dogs, but is especially important with dogs who will not come when called.)

Luci and Snickers are two easy going, well behaved girls who will make great companions for their new family.  They will be good girls while you are gone, they will be happy to see you when you are home, and they’re content to entertain themselves (with naps) when you’re busy. 

Interested in adding one of our adoptables to your family?  More information and our adoption application can be found at www.luluslockerrescue.org.

animal.description:
***AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION AT OUR FLORIDA LOCATION***

Coco is a 1 year old female Terrier mix. She weighs approximately 30lbs, is house trained and Hw+.

From her foster mom: Hello my name is Coco. I am a loving, playful, high energy pup, but can be very shy and submissive at first. My foster parents think some horrible humans were abusive to me in the past and I can get very scared thinking I will get yelled at. But I love to please! Once I warm up to you I will follow you everywhere and always want to play. I walk well on a leash and would love a home with another playful pup so we can wrestle and play all day long.

Coco, like so many of our adults and mommas that come in, is heartworm positive. This is NOT contagious and is not a death sentence! We have started her on Heartgard which will keep new worms from growing and allow the ones already present to die off slowly. This is the safest way to do it in the group home setting. It is a very manageable treatment plan. Included in her adoption is a year supply of Heartgard.

Coco is available in Bonifay, Florida through the rescue efforts of The Lucky Puppy Rescue. The minimum $250 adoption fee includes spay/neuter surgery, vaccinations, de-worm, flea prevention, heartworm prevention and martingale safety collar. Applications must be submitted through our website - theluckypuppy.org - thank you! You may copy and paste the following link to apply: http://www.theluckypuppy.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Tesla we believe to be a 10 month old female Shepherd / Labradoodle mix. We did a DNA test on her mom, and found out mom was a Labradoodle Shepherd mix. We believe dad must have been a Shepherd mix too. 

Tesla was a stray dog living in the woods under a collapsed house with her mom and a younger litter of half siblings. We were able to get the entire family to safety.

Tesla is a very sweet little girl, but is still afraid of humans. She will let you pet and hold her, but she will not willingly come to you for affection. When you do pet her, she will tuck her tail and lower her head as if she is afraid you will hurt her. She has the most soulful eyes, but they have zero spark to them. She is living life scared and unsure if she can trust. She has not shown aggression of any kind, she just trots away from you if she can. 

Tesla would do great in a home with another dog, as she bonds quickly with them, and follows their lead. She needs the security of another dog showing her that life with your humans can be an amazing thing. 

This wonderful little girl will melt your heart, and just needs a gentle hand and soft touch to help her become the confident little girl she was meant to be. If you have the loving home that Tesla is looking for please consider this wonderful little girl. You will not be disappointed and may just find the best friend you have ever had. 

To adopt please email puppyrescue911@yahoo.com and ask for an adoption application. All information about the adoption process will be emailed to you along with the application. A vet reference check and home visit will also be done prior to adoption.

All Rescue Kids are fully vetted prior to adoption and includes:  spay or neuter, vaccinations to prevent kennel cough, distemper, parvo and leptospirosis, rabies vaccination for those older than 16 weeks, microchipped, and dewormed. They are also heartworm tested and treated if positive. Eyes, ears and teeth checked and any necessary medical work done.
 
Pupppy Rescue 911 takes in dogs with many different medical issues. We are committed to providing our rescue dogs with top of the line Veterinary care. Please make a donation to help with our medical expenses. We are a non profit rescue with 100% of donations going to the care of these animals.
 
Donations can be made via Pay Pal to:
puppyrescue911@yahoo.com
 
Or directly towards our bill at:
Chester Animal Hospital
c/o Puppy Rescue 911
150 Taggart Lane
Chester IL. 62233-1001         
 
Adoption fees vary depending on specifics of each dog.

Lamar is a lab mix who is a bit on the squatty side, which makes him that much cuter because who can resist a big dog body and personality on some shorter legs? We know we can't! Lamar is about a year or so old and has not had the best of days, showing some hair loss and little signs that he hasn't had the TLC he so deserves. No worries, all of that TLC started the day he joined the farm here at SG and he has been living large, making friends and doing him. Lamar is about 40 to 45 lbs now and is a chunk of dog though still lean and in need of filling out moreagain something he is already working at. He is a fun loving dude who loves to play, wrestle and go full speed whenever the opportunity arises. Lamar would fit easily into a home with a like energy dog and would seriously be up for most anything with you and whatever pack of friends you bring along. He could throw down for a game of football, chase a basketball or try his paw at tennis if the conditions were right, athletic as he is. As much as he goes hard when he plays, Lamar can settle into a crate like a good boy and naps just as hard. Lamar would like to be your love muffin in 2021 and promises to make everyday happier and a little more, heck a lot more, fun!

animal.description:
Hi! I am Zena and am all that and a bag of tricks! Sit, down, stay, and go to kennel that is!
I love to learn and am an eager student so I would just love it if you took me to some reward-based training classes. I am basically a big puppy and still have some puppy behaviors like being a touch mouthy that I need to work on so maybe no younger kiddos for me. I also am working on play boundaries with other dogs as I am very intense and this is not always accepted by other dogs. I am fostered with cats and have done well, but I do chase them and try to get them to play so a kitty friend would have to be very tolerant of my shenanigans. I am doing well with house training in my foster home. I have a great on and off switch, meaning I can play, play, play when you want and then settle for snuggles on the couch. I love my tummy rubbed and can't wait to find a family who will give me attention! I am still recovering from demodex mange (not contagious) and am getting all of my beautiful fur back; my adoption can be completed when the Doc says I am good to go!

We do not have a facility for you to visit.

WE PROCESS APPLICANTS AND SET APPOINTMENTS BASED ON THE ORDER APPLICATIONS ARE RECEIVED

, so while you are welcome to email
ccrcdogs@ccrcdogs.com
with specific questions, you will want to complete the

ONLINE APPLICATION

ASAP

,

which can be found at www.ccrcdogs.com,

to secure your position in line for one of our dogs. You can also find

a description of our process on that same page. Puppies will not be available to be seen until their 10 day quarantine has passed. Our adoption fee is $200 for adults and $275 for puppies, which covers the cost of the spay/neuter, age appropriate shots and tests, medications to bring the dog to full health, and a free visit with one of our approved vets after adoption. The majority of dogs at CCRC are obtained from animal control centers, so there is often very little known about their history or even current habits. You can always expect to do some training, regardless of whether you adopt a dog or a puppy, including crate training, house training, and basic manners. CCRC provides a variety of materials and resources to assist you with this, as well as telephone support.

animal.description:
He may look like a bit like Wiley Coyote with his long legs and lanky body and he is likely to create a few laughs toobut other than that, this angel is all his own teenage self (with his own fancy name spelling) and cannot wait to grow up and grow into his new family! Wylie is about 10 months old and weighs around 40 lbs now, but he is on the lean side and still has more growing to do as well. A Dobie mix, likely along with a hound of some kind, Wylie is an eye catcher for sure! This young man is still a bit shy and unsure of himself, no surprise as he is still a teen and working to figure everything out including things he has not yet had any experience with. Wylie would love a doggo friend to help show him the way and/or people who would enjoy training activities and doing lots of things with him to help him build confidence and learn about the wonderful world of suburbia. Wylie is young and playful and is totally in the market for active folks who enjoy walks and even hikes on a regular basis. He has learned tons already about crate training and waiting for meals and is just waiting to take his A student skills on home with you and settle right in. Wylie will be a-waiting!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

Tofu is a Boxer mix boy that was born in October 2017 and weighs 53 pounds. 

Tofu is an all around affectionate and fun guy  fFriendly, cuddly, and playful. He’ll never pass up the opportunity to jump in your lap for cuddles on the couch or go for a nice walk around the neighborhood. He loves making new canine friends, but he can be a little rough and rowdy so a Meet & Greet is required if you have a dog at home. Tofu loves to play fetch and tag with his friends and would love to have family to romp around the yard with. Tofu is good with dogs and older kids. He may already be potty trained as he is able to hold it until we let him out of his kennel in the mornings.

We're open Wednesday - Sunday 12 - 5 p.m but are doing meet & greets and adoptions by appointment only.  

The adoption fee is $90 which includes a free veterinary exam within 2 weeks of adoption at local participating vets, up to date vaccinations, heartworm test,  heartworm preventative, dewormer, flea preventative, microchip, & spay or neuter.

animal.description:
We are in love with Lana! This big lovable puppy (10 months) is so affectionate, happy, huggable, and no one can resist her. Lana was all by herself 22 hours a day outside in her former home and she is dreaming about a family who will bring her into their hearts and home, spend lots of time with her and make her a big part of their life. She wants to be loved and she will love you right back in the best possible way. Lana loves all people including polite kids, she thinks other dogs are great as long as they are gentle like her. She will need a no cat and no chicken home. Lana was alone so much for the first part of her life and she tried very hard to develop her fence climbing skills so she could get out and look for friends so she wouldn't be so lonely. Her new family would need to stay outside with her, keep her on leash, or make sure their fence was at least 6 ft. Lana does not wander off if you are with her, but she goal is to be with the people she loves. Her pictures don't really capture how beautiful she is!
*If you are interested in adopting Lana please call the shelter (509 662-9577) to set up an appointment to meet her.

animal.description:
Timon is a very happy guy who loves nothing more than to run and play with any dog he meets (he likes to wrestle too!), but when that's over this 65-pound guy is happiest right in your lap. He is gentle taking food and loves to give kisses, he is truly a sweet cuddle bug and companion. He enjoys chewing his toys, and is working on stairs, learning his name, and how to sit. 

Timon would be great with a family or person who wants to put in time to help him learn even more - he is eager to please and responsive to feedback - he will be a quick student! Timon has high energy so may not be the best fit with older dogs or cats as his pure love of life may overwhelm them. He keeps up with his 2-year-old foster brother! Timon is 5 and no longer a puppy but I don't think anyone told him because he still has that goofy puppy excitement, he loves to do spins when he sees other dogs and play pounces on new exciting toys. If you are looking for a ball of fun to cuddle with at the end of the day, Timon would make the best companion.

If you would like to find out more, please contact 206fosters@gmail.com.

Hank Aaron is a Hound mix boy that was born in November 2019 and weighs 62 pounds. 

Hank is a special boy with a lot of love to give - happy, playful, and loveable. He had a rough start in his original home, but now we’re doing eerything we can to find him a place to finally call his forever home. We are not sure exactly what happened in his previous life, but as a result, he is a little fearful of men when first meeting them. He’s not aggressive, just shy. He prefers to sneak up behind you to sniff your ankles when you’re not looking and slowly introduce himself, however, he loves the (human) ladies and gets so excited to make new female friends. Once he gets his initial sniff to verify you’re a good person, he won’t leave you alone.

Hank's favorite thing to do is lean and stick to you like velcro. He’s very cuddly and just wants to be held and hugged. He is a little on the larger side and does have a lot to learn about being on a leash, but a well-sized harness and good strong leash will go a long way. He’s always excited to go for a car ride and will even offer to drive if you don’t want to. Hank loves to play with all sorts of toys or chew on a good antler or Benebone. He does love to make canine friends, but a Meet & Greet is required if you have a dog at home because he can be a little picky. Hank would do best in a home with a fenced-in backyard rather than an apartment and would do best with bigger kids/teenagers because he loves to give heavy hugs. 

 
We're open Wednesday - Sunday 12 - 5 p.m but are doing meet & greets and adoptions by appointment only.  

The adoption fee is $90 which includes a free veterinary exam within 2 weeks of adoption at local participating vets, up to date vaccinations, heartworm test,  heartworm preventative, dewormer, flea preventative, microchip, & spay or neuter.

If you are interested in this pet, please fill out our ADOPTION APPLICATION at https://goo.gl/forms/9FdDBiPU5aa5ySTv1

Visit our website at www.PetPlacementCenter.com

animal.description:
Dusty was found in west Texas and sat in an outdoor shelter for weeks waiting for a savior. When we picked him up, he was so skinny and had a lip injury we were very worried about initially. In 3 short weeks, this baby has already gained 9lbs and looks amazing. We learned from the vet that his lip injury was old, and had healed on its own. He was very lucky it didn’t get infected as it healed, but now he has the cutest pout we have ever seen.

Dusty is around 9 years old, and is now up to 50lbs. His favorite activity is rocking in the recliner with his foster dad. His foster mom describes him as super sweet, calm, and gentle. He gets along well with their their other dogs, as well as their children (9 and 4). He really loves affection, likes his kennel, and even walks well on a leash (no cats please). Overall, this sweet boy is pretty perfect. He does still need to complete his heart worm treatment, but that cost will be covered by our generous donors. Our goal is to find this sweetheart a family who will recognize the amazing boy he is, and allow him to be your best friend

Thanks for considering a Cane Rosso Rescue dog! 
We place dogs mostly in Texas but have adopted out a few out-of-state as well.
 
If you are interested in one of our dogs, please first complete our adoption application.
You can find it at https://www.canerossorescue.org/adoption-application . His adoption fee is $150 plus tax. Our dogs are spayed or neutered, microchipped, vaccinated and heartworm tested and treated (if tested positive) before going to a new home. For more information, visit our website www.canerossorescue.org
or email us at rescue@canerosso.com.

Did I catch your eye? Learn more about me by reading my profile below; I just might be your new best friend! Apply on our website
(

https://www.healingheartsrescue.org/adopt

)

to

set up a private meeting or check below for my adoption event schedule.

Age: Estimated DOB 11/20/20

Dog friendly: Yes

Cat friendly: Yes

Kid friendly: Yes

Potty trained: No, I'm just a puppy

Crate trained: No, I'm just a puppy

Juniper is a spunky little girl with lots of personality. She loves people, other dogs, and food of course! Playing with toys is also a fun hobby of hers but beware of items she might mistake for toys. That puppy teething business is no joke!

Juniper is working on potty training and doing well. She is a very smart girl and is quick to learn puppy basics. She has mastered sit and is almost an expert on lay down and roll over! This girl is sure to be a perfect addition to any loving family.

EXPERIENCED OWNER ONLY - NEEDS A STRONG PACK LEADER

Adoption Fee: $495

INTERESTED IN MEETING ME?

If you'd like to arrange a private meeting or begin the adoption process, please fill out an adoption application by visiting

https://www.healingheartsrescue.org/adopt

**Note on breed and age determination:

Breed and age are often determined on appearance, our own knowledge, veterinarian advice, and/or information from the sending shelters or previous owners. Most of our adoptable dogs were previously stray dogs with little history, we can't be 100% sure of a dog's breed mix, and unless there is a specific date of birth listed, we can't be 100% sure of a dog's age. Additionally, our assessments of a dog's interactions with other dogs, cats, or children are based on OUR experiences. Your experience may differ.

ADOPTION FEE INCLUDES:

Wellness check

Spay/neuter (puppies adopted with required spay/neuter certificate)

Age appropriate vaccines - rabies as required by law and distemper combo or proof of positive titer test

Heartworm test if over 7 months of age

Fecal test and/or deworming for parasites

Microchip



~ Healing Hearts rescue will also provide dental procedures, bloodwork, surgeries, and/or any other additional vet work as needed while dogs are in our care.

~ Adoption fees are non-negotiable and fees are listed on the dog's profile

~ Adoption fees can be paid the following ways with the required sales tax (7.525%) added:

PayPal

Credit Card

Cash

WANT TO HELP SAVE MORE DOGS?

Healing Hearts Rescue is a nonprofit, foster-based rescue

located in the Twin Cities area of Minnesota

that is 100% funded through adoption fees and donations

. We are excited for you to join us on this mission to save the lives of dogs in need.

We believe every dog deserves to be loved as true members of a family and are committed to fulfilling that dream one dog at a time! Sign up to foster, volunteer or donate on our
website

Healing Hearts rescue will also provide dental procedures, bloodwork, surgeries, and/or any other additional vet work as needed while dogs are in our care.

animal.description:
Meet Julie!

If you enjoy a companion who just wants to snuggle with you on the sofa, head in your lap watching TV, Julie is your girl. Julie is 8 years old and she weighs about 58 pounds. She is the sweetest, most loving dog a person could have. She will follow you into every room, lie down and wait for you to finish your chores. She will come and sit in front of you at attention and softly groan to let you know she wants food or a walk. So adorable! While she is a calm, coach potato inside, she is an enthusiastic walker outside, though she could use a bit more training on the leash. She loves her two walks a day, one after breakfast and one after diner. Although Julie is a quiet dog, she is a good watch dog. She will bark when someone comes to the door or in the yard. She will also alert you when she hears some noise in the house. In terms of environment, Julie will do better in a quiet house with calm teenagers and/or adults. She is truly a companion dog and won't be as happy if left alone all day as if someone were home with her. She does not like to be left alone in the yard either. Now, maybe if she had a companion dog, that might be different. In terms of a companion, Julie would do better with medium to large dogs although she may want most of the attention. She had two companion dogs when she was with her previous owner, one was male and the other female. So, if you are looking for a true companion who just wants to be with you, this loving, affectionate girl is waiting for you.

Albert's Dog Lounge is a transporting dog rescue, meaning that we rescue many of our dogs from high kill shelters in areas of dog overpopulation. We are a specialty rescue focusing primarily on senior and special needs dogs.  The vast majority of our dogs come from the Houston, TX area where we have an entire team of volunteers, coordinators, and fosters. We do also work with local shelters, rescues, and owners.  If you apply for a dog that is currently in our local Houston program, we will work to get your dog transported to WI as quickly as possible. We ask that you have patience during this time of uncertainty and unprecedented dog adoptions nationwide. 

Learn more about Albert's Dog Lounge, our mission, and adoption policies by visiting Albertsdoglounge.org. 

Our process includes an approved application, reference checks, a homevisit, and then a meet and greet with the dog. Adoption fee is $275.

Begin your application process by copying this link into your web browser: https://www.albertsdoglounge.org/apply

WI Dept. Of Agriculture License Number: 474085-DS
