animal.description:
Say hello to your new best friend!

Canelo is a very young Anatolian Shepard/Husky mix. Canelo is the most active of the pups, is very playful and love cuddling with his siblings. He is one pup from a litter of 9 to their husky mom. 

Canelo's mama produced a few litters for her caretakers before being dumped and left to fend for herself. Her rescuer discovered she was expecting before they could get her spayed and asked POPP for help. Mama (Luna) and all her pups have been well cared for and are now ready to start lives with their furever families. 

Both Huskies and Anatolian Shepherds have some unique breed traits so we are looking for people familiar with the breeds. 

If you are interested in adopting Canelo, his adoption fee is $200. He will be neutered, microchipped and vaccines started. Here is a link to our adoption questionnaire: https://www.popptricities.org/adopt/adoption-questionnaire-canine/

Snoop and his littermates were found roaming in rural Texas. They are now learning the ins and outs of life in a foster home. They are about 3 months old currently. We think they are likely a mix of a lot of breeds, including cattle dog and terrier mixes. We think they will likely be between 55-70 pounds when full grown.

They are getting experience living with other dogs but haven't yet spent significant time with kids or cats.

Puppies need someone with the time, energy and patience for house-training and basic obedience. 

Puppies under 6 months of age are adopted out on a spay/neuter contract

Our adoption fee includes age appropriate vaccinations, deworming, microchipping and transport expenses. Adoption fee is $450 to help offset travel and medical expenses.

All children at home should be at least age 5 to be approved for adoption!

animal.description:
Seattle Foster Update :

Jack is a friendly outgoing guy! He happily greets new people & dogs. He is looking for a home without kids. Jack knows how to sit already! He also loves to give lots of kisses.

Jack is fairly energetic, but he also loves to relax and snuggle -- so overall, mid level energy.

Jack is good in the crate and he sometimes goes in on his own, but otherwise can be tempted with a treat. Jack rides well in the car.

While Jack is not much of barker, he does like to talk -- sometimes when anxious or sometimes when bored -- pretty typical of what's in his breed mix!

Jack does need some work on his leash training. He is very focused on sniffing outside, so sometimes he can pull to get to a spot, and doesn't always come when asked (to continue sniffing a spot). Again, hounds are very nose oriented, but this can be worked on.

Jack likes solo play, mostly chewing & fetch, so he would be fine as the only dog in the home, and may even prefer it. He likes kongs! He has played a bit with our resident dog & seems open to it, but we'll know more as his personality comes out.

He likes to be the center of attention and can get jealous of our resident dog receiving attention. He is respectful of boundaries, including with resident dog though

Animal Profile:
Jack is an estimated 6-year-old 44 lb male Terrier/Hound mix who will be joining us from Hawaii on January 27th. He is energetic and playful with dogs and loves people. He is looking for an active home without children. We will post more info as we get to know hi

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $475, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, heartworm test, and flight from Hawaii. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was transferred from our Kauai Humane Society rescue partner. This dog will be available for adoption in Seattle once evaluated.

Animal Profile: Bruce is an estimated 3 year old 52lb Lab/Rottweiler mix who joined us from a high-kill shelter in California on January 24th. Bruce is the most laid back, chill dude. His favorite activities include leisurely walks, long naps and scratchies. He loves his humans and tolerates other dogs well but does not prefer their company. Bruce currently lives with a fur foster sister but would prefer to be an only dog in his forever home. He is not especially playful or energetic, he would do well in any type of home, including an apartment as long as he gets his walkies for bathroom breaks. Bruce has a quiet, introverted nature and can be grumpy at times so we do not feel he would be the best match in a home with young children. He is crate trained and does super well on leash. He also does well when left alone and just sleeps in his crate. Bruce would like nothing more than to be your most devoted best friend!

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue. Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in California and will be available for adoption in Seattle, once evaluated in a loving foster home in the greater Seattle area.

animal.description:
4m old Mai & Tai from South Carolina are absolutely inseparable and no, we aren't separating, so please apply if you want a good and hers matching set of the cutest beagles we've ever had the pleasure of loving.

Facebook: Zani's Furry Friends ZFF (weekly adoption event info posted there)
Twitter: zanisff 
Instagram: zanisfurryfriends
 
Dogs are spayed/neutered, UTD on age appropriate vaccines, Rabies vaxed, and microchipped (not Lyme vaxed but we seriously recommend it!)  All are in the NY/NJ area but we will adopt out of state to the purrfect home and in some cases, we can arrange transport.  Please go to our site zanisfurryfriends.org  and fill out an application 

Many of us (cats/dogs) will be on display on Saturdays or Sundays, weather dependent--please ask by writing us at info@zanisfurryfriends.org and following us on FB. If you are seriously interested in adopting one of us in particular, please fill out an application early Friday so that we can be sure to be there. Otherwise we decide based on other variables. Usually we are in our foster homes so this is a bit more stressful and a slightly artificial environment but we do want to be seen and find our furever homes too.
 
Please consider providing a home for more than one dog, especially if you are considering adopting a puppy. Dogs are pack animals and very much enjoy as well as need other dog company to learn to play, socialize and be good companion animals to people. The upside to this is that you won't feel as guilty leaving them alone and you get twice the love. Please come! And if you can't adopt, maybe you can foster or volunteer, and you can always donate!

animal.description:
DUFFY is a sweet playful senior who is great with cats and other dogs. He has been taken care of very well and had regular vet visits and nail trims. His elderly guardian died in her sleep. His family consists of another small Jack Russel mix that he is quite fond of Hattie - they are a bonded pair and must adopt together;  a medium sized dog (Moki) and two cats (Panda is seen together with Duffy often, they are fond of each other). We are looking for a family that will love them and continue their excellent veterinary care. Duffy is 10 yrs old, neutered, microchipped and vaccinated. Hattie is 11 yrs old, spayed, vaccinated, microchipped. They're currently eating Marty's Meals.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
Howdy I'm Elizabeth!!!

I'm a sweet little girl that loves to cuddle all while playing and doing all those puppy things. I was saved from an overcrowded shelter along with all my brothers and sisters. I currently love playing with my bigger foster sister while exploring all the amazing things this world brings (especially all the tree branches ?) 

I was born dec. 21 and working on my puppy manners, foster mommy says I learn very quickly. Right now I am about 5lbs and expected to be medium to large size full grown given my mix breed. I love kids and other dogs, I've seen cats and they don't bother me (I even have a squirrel friend ). Lastly foster mommy is working on Kennel training with me and its going very well I think I'll be a pro very soon ?.

Overall I'm a spunky, lovable girl that has lots of love to give I can't wait to join your family to start making all those great memories... are you excited to meet me?? Hurry and apply I can't wait to meet my forever family!

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

animal.description:
HATTIE is a sweet senior who is great with cats and other dogs. She has been taken care of very well and had regular vet visits and monthly acupuncture visits as well. Her elderly guardian died in her sleep. Her family consists of another small Jack Russel mix (Duffy) that she is quite fond of (they are a bonded pair and must adopt together), a medium sized dog (Moki) and four cats. We are looking for a family that will love Hattie and Duffy and continue their excellent veterinary care. Hattie is on a medication and Chinese herbs due to a mitral valve and cataracts. She is 11 yrs old, spayed, microchipped and vaccinated. Duffy is a playful 10 yr old, vaccinated, neutered, and microchipped. They are currently eating Marty's Meals.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

*PLEASE NOTE: JAKE WILL NEED A FOREVER HOME WITH A YARD*

Jake is a 7 month old neutered male Decker Rat Terrier who weighs 24 lbs. Jake came to All 4 Paws after his owner could no longer provide him the care he needed due to health problems. This active boy is looking for an equally active family. He loves to play, be outside, and explore. Due to his activity level Jake is looking for a home with a yard in which he can stretch his legs. Jake is super smart and knows how to ring bells when he has to go outside. He seems to be house broken, is good in a crate, and listens well, but still needs a little work on leash. Jake would do best in a home without young kids as he does get excited and jump up still. He's been great with other dogs in play groups and loves playing with his doggie pals. He'll need a home without cats though. This adorable little guy is affectionate and cannot wait to find the devoted forever family he deserves - could it be yours??

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/

Hi my name is Xavier. I'm just over a year old and weigh about 60 lbs. I'm a black lab mix and my foster mom says I'm the cutest and sweetest.   

I get along great with kids, cats,  and especially other dogs. I even like to go to my foster parents barn and hang out with the horses and cows. I relaxed and chill around people but don't demand a lot of attention. I just want to be in the room with you. Foster mom says my personality really comes out around my dog friends and I'd love a furrever home that has a friend for me.  

I just learned to walk on a leash and am fully potty trained. I'm also crate trained but sometimes need a treat bribery to go in. I ride well in a vehicle and enjoy going to the office everyday with my foster daddy. I do have one naughty habit I haven't gotten rid of,  I do enjoy counter surfing for snacks and investigating the trash in detail.  

I had heartworm but have been fully treated and am scheduled to be neutered soon. Do you want to be my furrever home? I can't wait to meet you!!

animal.description:
Wow that was close! You see after being dumped in the country I almost got hit by a truck but some nice lady picked me up like a football and saved me. Bye-bye Clovis New Mexico hello Colorado. My name is Chloe and I’m wondering if you’re my forever. I’m about five months old, 24 lbs and possibly a Dalmatian mix. I’m amazingly well adjusted and outgoing for my scary beginnings. I’m curious on my walks and want to say hello to all those new people and pups. I love to play with the dogs in my foster home and would do best with another playful companion that doesn’t get annoyed if I occasionally don’t take their cues that they’re done. I’m pretty energetic so a yard and a good amount of exercise are recommended. I am good at playing with toys on my own and love snuggling; I’m a well rounded girl. After a little bit of protesting I sleep nicely in my crate all night. I’m very close to housebroken; it’s just a new house I’m a little confused. I pretty much love everybody; since I still have a bit of that puppy mouthing and razor blade teeth really young children probably wouldn’t be a great idea. Well enough about me what about you? Would you want to wake up every day with a pup who is a true joy to be around? I promise I’ll make you smile and be a really good girl if you are the right home for me. animal.description:
MOKI is a sweet senior who is great with cats and other dogs. He has been taken care of very well and had regular vet visits and monthly acupuncture visits as well. He is also accustomed to regular brushings and nail trims. His elderly guardian died in her sleep. His fur family consists of two smaller dogs (Hattie and Duffy) and two cats (Panda). We are looking for a family that will love him and continue his excellent veterinary care. He is on a medication - Thyrosin. He is 11 yrs old, neutered, microchipped and vaccinated.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
Olive and Ivy are  Chiweenie sisters born in August of 2020. They each weigh 12 lbs and originally came from a home where they were left outside with very little human interaction and were very shy and scared. They were then adopted by a lovely older couple who potty trained them and gave them lots of loving and attention. But very sad to say they are now dealing with a terminal illness and had to return the pups. 
Ivy is the white one, very friendly, loving, sweet and has tons of energy!
Her sister Olive is the shy black one. She is afraid of strangers and will shriek, growl or pee on herself if scared.  You just have to ignore her and approach slowly and she will be fine and loving and sweet like her sister! 
The girls play with each other non stop! Very bonded pair and must be adopted together.


Adoption fee includes spaying/neutering, shots, micro-chip and deworming.
Please contact foster parent Dinesha at 972-896-6313 or email adbadoptions@yahoo.com. To see dogs, please download an application from our website, www.adifferentbreed.org and email it to foster parents address above. We will arrange a meet and greet.

animal.description:
MEET Woodhouse!  
1/31 update:  Please note, we are looking for adopters who currently have outgoing, socialized dogs for this pup and two of his siblings.  Because they are so fearful, they will need another dog to show them the way and help them come out of their shells.  Adopters will need to have lots of patience and give them plenty of time to adapt.

Woodhouse is a 14-week old Labrador/Hound mix pup who was rescued in VA from a farm with many other dogs. He has been in foster now and is developing good house manners and has made good progress with potty training but will need a continued routine. 

When full-grown, he will be a large dog. He would do best in a home who will provide positive reinforcement puppy training. We don't know how he will do with cats.

All of our dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations & microchipped.
We strive to make the best match possible for each and every dog we place.  If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out the online application (copy and paste into your browser) https://forms.gle/rv5JfMurqAeVJQc98
Or if you have questions, please email: traveling4pawsadopt@gmail.com.

animal.description:
Meet the infamous tiktok song litter! Chicken Wing, Chicken Wing, Hotdog & Bologna! Chicken & Macaroni, Chillin’ with my Homies! 

These 2 month old lab chihuahua mixes are ready to move on from their life of fame and settle into a forever home! These guys weigh between 3-8 lbs and will be small dogs when fully grown. They have typical puppy energy, enjoying wrestling matches with each other and chewing on bones, before settling in for a nap. Chillin & Homie are the smallest of the litter. They’re sweet pups who are ready for their forever family! Their adoption fee is $400.00.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
Let's see, here's a list of what I LOVE: to play ALOT, run ALOT, chew ALOT, eat ALOT.  And here is a list of things I NEED: LOTS of walks, which means leash training, LOTS of toys, so I can chew my own stuff, LOTS of socializing with people and other animals, that way we can both have lots of friends, LOTS of training, which requires LOTS of patience, but pays off when you realize it makes me so much easier to live with and last but not least, LOTS of Love.   Yeah, I admit it, I'm a lot of work at first, but trust me, we'll both find it to be worth the effort.  Only those who can handle all of the above and intend to keep me with them no matter what life may bring need apply.  

Animals in our program are housed in Foster homes. Please contact us @ 208-232-0371, leave a message and a Volunteer will get back with you as soon as possible, with the Foster Parent's contact information.

Visit with this animal and our other fosters during our Adoption day, the second Saturday of each month @ our building, located @ 850 Barton Rd., Pocatello, ID 83204
